# Supabase Stripe Sync Engine Reference

**GA: January 2026**

Stripe Sync Engine creates live Postgres replicas of your Stripe data — customers, subscriptions, invoices, products, and payments — queryable as regular SQL tables. Replaces manual webhook sync for read operations.

---

## Setup — One Click

```
Dashboard → Integrations → Stripe Sync Engine → Enable
  → Enter Stripe Secret Key
  → Select which objects to sync (customers, subscriptions, invoices, products, prices)
  → Supabase creates a private stripe_sync schema

IMPORTANT: stripe_sync schema is PRIVATE — never exposed via PostgREST.
Access only via server-side code with service_role, or via SQL functions with SECURITY DEFINER.
```

---

## Available Tables

```sql
-- After enabling, these tables exist in the stripe_sync schema:
stripe_sync.customers        -- Stripe customer objects
stripe_sync.subscriptions    -- Subscription objects + status
stripe_sync.subscription_items  -- Individual subscription line items
stripe_sync.invoices         -- Invoice objects + payment status
stripe_sync.invoice_items    -- Line items on invoices
stripe_sync.prices           -- Price objects
stripe_sync.products         -- Product objects
stripe_sync.payment_intents  -- Payment intent objects
stripe_sync.payment_methods  -- Payment method objects
stripe_sync.charges          -- Charge objects

-- Check sync status
SELECT table_name, last_sync_at FROM stripe_sync.sync_status;
```

