## Stripe Sync Engine vs Manual Webhooks

| | Stripe Sync Engine | Manual Webhooks |
|---|---|---|
| Setup | One click | Write webhook handler + RLS + tables |
| Read operations | Use SQL directly | Query your own synced tables |
| Write operations | Still use Stripe API | Use Stripe API |
| Data freshness | Near real-time (~seconds) | Immediate (webhook fires on event) |
| Historical data | Backfills all history | Only what you received |
| Use for | Analytics, dashboards, admin queries | Fulfillment, email triggers, status updates |

**Recommendation:** Use Sync Engine for read/query operations. Keep webhooks for write-triggered side effects (send confirmation email when subscription created, update app access when subscription cancels).
